To create a React component, you can use either a function or a class. Here's a simple functional component:

```jsx
function MyComponent() {
  return <div>Hello World</div>;
}
```

Sure! Here's a component that accepts props:

```jsx
function Greeting({ name }) {
  return <div>Hello, {name}!</div>;
}
```

You can use it like: `<Greeting name="Alice" />`
